The paper deals with a decentralized Time Division Multiple Access (TDMA) technique for network nodes, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The algorithm is inspired by the dynamics of Pulse Coupled Oscillators (PCO), which is a topic in dynamical systems (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the convergence of the algorithm, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
